lead_paragraph: An article on Tuesday about the players who starred in the final scheduled game at Yankee Stadium against the Baltimore Orioles on Sunday night misstated the score in the fourth inning when the Yankees’ José Molina hit what would become the last home run at the ballpark. It was tied, 3-3; the Yankees were not trailing by a run.
